# {{substub}}--[[User:CentralVac Guru|CentralVac Guru]] 19:39, 1 August 2006 (UTC)
Definition:
A vacuum cleaner whereby a main tank is located in a remote location such as a garage, basement or closet.  A series of tubes lead to various inlet valve locations located throughout the home.  A lightweight 30 foot (9 meter) hose is plugged into the inlet and the user will then attach various attachments for cleaning.